## Proposal

### Please re-state the problem that we are trying to solve in this issue.
A different group chat is opened when we refresh while we have opened profile detail of group chat member
### What is the root cause of that problem?
When we open profile detail of a member of a group chat the route is changed to '.../a/memberID or ParticipantID' so the report id is lost from the url, hence when we refresh the last group chat reportId will be populated to ReportScreen via ReportIDSetter in the below code
https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/7b546b0470b34bcaf5b9ee85e5011fff42443fc4/src/libs/Navigation/AppNavigator/ReportScreenIDSetter.js#L85-L87
which sets the reportID to the id returned from `ReportUtils.findLastAccessedReport` which does not reliably return the id of last opened report by the user.
### What changes do you think we should make in order to solve the problem?
<!-- DO NOT POST CODE DIFFS -->
We need to save a stack of latest opened report ids the user opened in onyx everytime a user opens a report. Then we will populate the latest available report id from the stack in the `ReportScreenIDSetter` changing this line of code
https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/7b546b0470b34bcaf5b9ee85e5011fff42443fc4/src/libs/Navigation/AppNavigator/ReportScreenIDSetter.js#L85-L87
to 
```
        const lastOpendAvailableID = _.find(lastOpenedReportIDs, (reportID) => _.find(reports, (report) => report.reportID === reportID));
        // If there is no reportID in route, try to find last accessed and use it for setParams
        const reportID =
            lastOpendAvailableID || getLastAccessedReportID(reports, !canUseDefaultRooms, policies, isFirstTimeNewExpensifyUser, lodashGet(route, 'params.openOnAdminRoom', false));

```
after passing lastOpenedReportIDs prop via `withOnyx` here
```
export default withOnyx({
    lastOpenedReportIDs: {
        key: ONYXKEYS.LAST_OPENED_REPORT_IDS,
    },
```
So we will only fallback to the existing `ReportUtils.findLastAccessedReport`  logic/code only in case when there is no available report id value saved in that new key ('LAST_OPENED_REPORT_IDS') we will create in onyx. 
We can update the 'LAST_OPENED_REPORT_IDS' value on onyx in a `useEffect` on ReportScreen that runs when there is a change in `reportID` and save up to say 10 recent opened ids which will serve us to be a back up in case last opened report id doesn't exist or got deleted.
```
     
    useEffect(() => {
        if (!_.isEmpty(reportID)) {
            const updatedLastOpenedIDs = _.clone(lastOpenedReportIDs || []);

            // to limit the no of ids saved to 10
            if (updatedLastOpenedIDs.length === 10) updatedLastOpenedIDs.pop();
            updatedLastOpenedIDs.unshift(reportID);
            Onyx.merge(ONYXKEYS.LAST_OPENED_REPORT_IDS, updatedLastOpenedIDs);
        }
    }, [reportID]);

```
Moreover, we need to clear that value on onyx on signout so that a report ids saved for one user will not be used for another.

POC:

https://github.com/Expensify/App/assets/38649957/798cb6bf-74ca-4e9c-8e45-6657ca59d1ee



### What alternative solutions did you explore? (Optional)
 or we can alternatively update the value in onyx every time the user navigates to a report.

